# honeycache

A caching layer that doubles as a honeypot. It keeps hot keys fast and quietly fingerprints anything that looks like enumeration.

## why

Most caches throw away the most interesting signal — *who asked for what, and how often*. honeycache keeps a tiny rolling profile per client and uses it to decide what is worth keeping.

```c
bool cache_should_keep(struct entry *e) {
  return e->hits > 2 || e->source_is_suspicious;
}
```

Single static binary, eBPF for the fast path, sqlite for the slow truth.
